Minister of Communications and Digital Technologies Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams provides update on key priorities, announce portfolio changes and institutional capacity building across the departments and entities. JOHANNESBURG - The EFF is laying criminal charges against Minister of Communications and Digital Technologies Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams and former MP Mduduzi Manana. Party spokesperson, Vuyani Pambo, will lay charges at Douglasdale Police Station. READ: Lockdown: Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams apologises to SA It comes after Ndabeni-Abrahams broke the lockdown regulations by visiting Manana at his house. President Cyril Ramaphosa placed Ndabeni-Abrahams on special leave for two-months with one being unpaid. The DA meanwhile says the special leave is the easy way out. READ: COVID-19 death toll rises to 13, confirmed cases to 1,749 The party says Ramaphosa should send out a strong message to the public by both firing her and laying a criminal complaint against her. The ANC welcomed her suspension. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.